# Trivy misconfig findings deliberately not "fixed" in the Dockerfile itself.
# (Trivy is not wired into CI; this file documents decisions for anyone
# running `trivy config .` ad hoc.)

# DS-0002 (no USER directive): privileges are dropped at startup instead.
# Pre-existing fleet volumes are root-owned, so a static USER would break
# them on redeploy; scripts/docker-entrypoint.sh starts as root, fixes /data
# ownership incrementally, then re-execs as the unprivileged `loomem` user
# (uid 10001) via gosu.
DS-0002

# DS-0026 (no HEALTHCHECK): the deployment platform (Railway) performs its
# own HTTP health checks and ignores Dockerfile HEALTHCHECK directives.
DS-0026
